{
  "stem": "21308.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was commanding my own unit as a major, and I'd been doing that since June, 1942.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ah, well, they gave me a new number then. 140218.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had-- still had my identity labels.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'll show them to you later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, after our battle outside Belsen concentration camp, we headed for the Elbe River, and we fondly believed the war for us would finish when we reached the Elbe and that the Russians would meet us on the Elbe.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were all quite pleased when, in actual fact, about the 21st of-- somewhere around about the 21st of April, we actually reached the Elbe opposite Lowenberg.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we started cleaning ourselves up, and we had inspections and church services.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then all of a sudden, my colonel grabbed me one day and said, come on, Ted, pick up your map case.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There's a war on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went along to see the commander brigadier, his orders group, and he told us that for political reasons, we had to get to the Baltic.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He was a very able soldier, and I admired him intensely.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we got along like a house on fire.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I thought when he introduced his orders, for political reasons we've got to get to the Baltic as soon as possible.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There couldn't be a better way of opening up, when I went back to see my chaps, my orders group were the same words.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so anyway, we-- we had the orders group with the brigadier, and he briefed me for what he wanted.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I raised one or two points on the spot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He didn't agree with half of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "However, events proved him to be right.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But then we crossed the River Elbe.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
